
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

- renamed feature_alignment.py to tric_alignment.py
- the following parameters were re-named for tric_alignment.py:
  
  max_rt_diff -> fixed_rt_diff
  max_rt_diff_units -> fixed_rt_diff_units
  iso_max_rt_diff -> iso_fixed_rt_diff
  realign_method -> rt_alignment
  max_fdr_quality -> fdr_extension_cutoff
  alignment_score -> rt_anchor_score
  mst:Stdev_multiplier -> adaptive_rtdiff_multiplier
  method -> tric_method
  fdr_cutoff -> fixed_seeding_cutoff

- the following parameters were re-named for requantAlignedValues.py:
  
  realign_runs -> rt_alignment
  method -> transfer_method

Furthermore, the default values were changed to 

- "lowess" (for rt_alignment)
- "LocalMST" (for tric_method) 
- "3.0" (for adaptive_rtdiff_multiplier) 
- "True" (for mst:useRTCorrection)
- "-1" (for fixed_seeding_cutoff)
- 0.01 (for target_fdr)

to reflect the parameters used in the TRIC paper.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Release 0.4.0
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

- improved reporting in YAML format for alignment tools
- port of code to Python 3
- option to use reference-based approach in MST algorithm
- improvements to documentation

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Release 0.3.2
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

- improvements in parsing of Peakview files (preprocessor script)
- multiple improvements in TAPIR
- creation of executables for TAPIR
- metabolomics support for TAPIR

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Release 0.3.0
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

- add tree-based alignment (MST options)
- improved output reporting
- add documentation
- improve test coverage substantially

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Release 0.2.0
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

- add TAPIR visualization tool for chromatograms
- output data matrix in Excel format

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Release 0.1.0
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

- initial version of library and alignment tools

